JOHANNESBURG – Entertainment Weekly has obtained an exclusive promo of upcoming movie Oscar Pistorius: Blade Runner Killer. The film, detailing Olympian and Paralympian Oscar Pistorius’s life, will premier in the United States on 11 November but no date has yet been given for the local release. READ: Oscar Pistorius let out of jail for gran's funeral Actor Andreas Damm will play the role of the double amputee, while Toni Garrn will play the role of his murdered girlfriend Reeva Steenkamp. The movie will tell the full story leading up to the fatal Valentine’s Day shooting in which Steenkamp was brutally murdered. Pistorius is serving a six-year prison sentence for the crime. READ: SCA to hear Pistorius appeal Here’s Entertainment Weekly’s exclusive promo: eNCA